# Canonical origin for sitemap, canonical URLs, and sharing (production: https://www.turnberryplaceforsale.com)
NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://www.turnberryplaceforsale.com

# Optional: Google Search Console — HTML tag verification (value only, not the full meta tag)
# See GSC_SETUP.md §1b for DNS TXT verification as the preferred alternative.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_SITE_VERIFICATION=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IndexNow — Bing/Yandex/Seznam/Naver notification endpoint
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required only to enable the POST /api/indexnow route. Any sufficiently
# random string; rotate if ever leaked. When unset, the endpoint returns 503.
# Google does NOT support IndexNow (and doesn't need it — relies on sitemap
# <lastmod>). See GSC_SETUP.md §4 for the full workflow.
# INDEXNOW_AUTH_TOKEN=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google Business Profile — Reviews CTA
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Target GBP (pending verification as of 2026-04-18) — the 20th location
# in the Dr. Jan Duffy portfolio, following the verified sibling-listing
# naming pattern used across the other 19 offices:
#
#   Turnberry Place High Rise Condos | Homes by Dr. Jan Duffy
#   2827 Paradise Rd, Suite 2, Las Vegas, NV 89109  (Suite 2, 1st floor, staffed office)
#
# The business name + street address in lib/reviews.ts `CANONICAL_NAP`
# matches the new GBP exactly. When unset, the "View Google Reviews" /
# "Write a Review" CTAs fall back to a Google Maps Search URL built from
# that NAP, which will resolve automatically to the new GBP the moment
# Google verifies it -- no code change required on verify day.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# WHILE THE GBP IS PENDING VERIFICATION (Google takes days to weeks):
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Set the following in Vercel → Settings → Environment Variables so the
# CTAs don't send visitors to a disambiguation page or the HOA-owned
# Turnberry Place building listing during the pending window:
#
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_GBP_REVIEWS_DISABLED=true
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# WHEN THE GBP IS VERIFIED:
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#   1. Remove NEXT_PUBLIC_GBP_REVIEWS_DISABLED (or set to "false") in
#      Vercel. The Maps search URL fallback will resolve directly to the
#      new GBP with zero code changes.
#
#   2. (Optional, recommended) Grab the place_id from Google's Place ID
#      Finder:
#        https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/places/web-service/place-id#find-id
#      ...and paste it into NEXT_PUBLIC_GBP_PLACE_ID in Vercel. The helper
#      auto-builds both read and write URLs, upgrading the CTA from
#      "Maps panel" to a deep-link into the reviews tab.
#
#   3. (Alternative) Open GBP dashboard → Customers → Reviews → "Get more
#      reviews" → copy the g.page/r/... short link into
#      NEXT_PUBLIC_GBP_WRITEREVIEW_URL for a pre-opened review form.
#
# Explicit URL env vars take precedence over NEXT_PUBLIC_GBP_PLACE_ID.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GBP_REVIEWS_URL=https://search.google.com/local/reviews?placeid=ChIJxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GBP_WRITEREVIEW_URL=https://search.google.com/local/writereview?placeid=ChIJxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GBP_PLACE_ID=ChIJxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# Hide both CTAs entirely without removing code (pending verification or
# during any GBP migration):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GBP_REVIEWS_DISABLED=true

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google Business Profile — AggregateRating (review-star SERP snippets)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# When BOTH of the following are set in Vercel, the RealEstateAgent and
# ApartmentComplex JSON-LD graphs emit an AggregateRating block. Google
# uses this to award review-star snippets on search result pages.
#
# Per CLAUDE.md and the global no-fabricated-social-proof rule, these
# values MUST come from the verified GBP dashboard, not estimates or
# round numbers. Invalid values (ratingValue outside 1-5, or non-integer
# reviewCount) are treated as absent so the schema stays valid.
#
# Typical sourcing:
#   1. Open Google Business Profile -> Customers -> Reviews (overview tile).
#   2. Read the averaged star rating (e.g. "5.0") and the count ("47 reviews").
#   3. Paste those into the two env vars below in Vercel.
#
# Google's threshold for actually displaying stars on a SERP is typically
# 5+ reviews on the entity. Setting these before you hit that threshold
# is harmless -- Google just won't render stars yet.
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GBP_AGGREGATE_RATING_VALUE=5.0
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GBP_AGGREGATE_RATING_COUNT=47

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google Maps JS API — interactive map (/map page only)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required ONLY by pages/map.tsx (interactive map with place markers).
# NOT required by the site-wide <GBPMapCard> iframe embed, which uses the
# public /maps?q=... endpoint and works without a key.
#
# Restrict this key in Google Cloud Console:
#   - HTTP referrer allowlist: *.turnberryplaceforsale.com/*
#   - APIs: "Maps JavaScript API", "Places API"
# When unset, the /map page renders a graceful "map pending" state.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=

